      What are people saying about food in Washington, DC?

      This is a review for food in Washington, DC:

      "Le Diplomate sets the standard for fine dining in DC. Even at their busiest, the service and food are consistently of the highest quality. The packed restaurant oozes energy and brings a real European vibe to 14th street. It's a thing of beauty to watch Rockstar servers like Chakib (over a decade at Le Dip) gracefully side through the crowds supported by solid managers like Peter, Charlie, and Ben (and maybe others) while Chef Greg makes magic in the kitchen. Like everyone else, I highly recommend."
